                              Editorial
========================================================================
    We have decided to attempt a Fidocon next summer, here in
net 221 (South Western Ontario).   Cory Albrecht, one of the
local net people, has started a host BBS to co-ordinate it, and
we have started a local echo for planning.  Currently, the echo
is being distributed to half a dozen nets in South Western
Ontario.  Hopefully, it will soon be getting much wider
distribution.

    What are we attempting to do?  Basically, we want a chance
for all fidonet members to meet as many net friends as is
possible.  At the least, Max and I are going to have one heck
of a big party here next August.  At best, those of you who
always wanted to visit Canada will be able to make all your
holiday plans by netmail ... we will get several information BBSes
set up for everything from art gallery tours to camping and
fishing, and about 5-600 families will start or end their
holidays here in Kitchener.

     So read Cory's article, and start planning ...

