Re-engineering of Net 700
Chris Leung (6:700/703 aka 6:700/0)

Please be informed that due to the following chaotic situations,
Net700 will be dissolved and restarted afresh in order to get
everything back to order.

1.  The former Network Coordinator (NC) still claims publicly that he
    is the N700C and continues to issue new node numbers to new sysops.
    He makes his own version of local nodelist and delivers it through
    the mail routing hubs to current fido sysops.  With the help of
    the current Network Echomail Coordinator (NEC), the fact of the
    re-appointment of N700C by the RC is being denied and totally
    concealed from all Net700 members.

2.  Although notice has been issued to the NEC and HUBs about the
    change of NC,  they still refuse to accept this fact.  They are
    unwilling to cooperate with the new NC.  Even worse, the NEC
    together with the mail routing hubs help distribute a fake
    international nodelist to all fido members.  Although attempts
    have been made to deliver the genuine international nodelists to
    all sysops via HUBs, it seems that none gets delivered
    successfully.  As per POLICY 4, such behaviour is considered to
    be excessively annoying.

3.  Many current sysops refuse to accept the decision and appointment
    made by the RC.  Being fido sysops, they should have read and
    agree to abide by FidoNet Policy currently in force.  In other
    words, they should know and understand the procedures for NC
    appointment. Failing to do so is considered to be failing to
    observe POLICY 4.

The trouble stirred up the former NC+NEC party causes serious
annoyance to many users.  In view of this, the current structure of
Net700 has to be dissolved and re-established.  Details will be made
available to Net700 sysops and users...

FidoNet is for fun, not for any power struggle!
FidoNet is for friendship, not for making any enemy!
FidoNet is for free communication, not for any censorship or control!
FidoNet is for all, not just for any *C!

Thank you very much for your attention, and let's sing requiem to
the chaotic Net700!

